This is from our article:
Registered Nurses - will have authorised access to a read-only view of the information detailed below in 'What is in GP Connect? section' found here.

Non clinical roles - will have authorised access to a read-only filtered view. The tabs for the filtered view provides access to allergies and adverse reactions, medications, immunisations and summary page. Roles include.

  • Registered Manager
  • Care Manager
  • Deputy Home Manager
  • Deputy Care Manager
  • Senior Carer
  • Team Leader
  • Social Worker

If you want to see GP Connect you will need to create a second account for viewing this information.
A Superuser is not allowed to view this information

If interactions recorded on the app are not showing on other devices then the app may have pending data.
​
Can you please confirm if there is pending data on the device
​(This can be seen by going to the side menu / 3 bars top left, scrolling down till you see pending <number>)


If there is pending please click "I have pending data" below 🙂

Who is logged in on the device?
(please use the options below 🙂⬇️)

Please can you go to administration and press backup (this will not clear the pending data)
​
If this doesn't reach 100% and say successful please check if the device is connected to WiFi and then try again.
​
Once the backup is done please do not record anything else on the device as it will not be included within the backup.
​﻿(The device will still have pending data after the backup)

Awesome, can you please, exit the app and Do Not Logout, reboot the phone (power button pressed for 3 secs and select restart) then when it's back on wait for 5 min, enter the app and click the log out button, wait there 2 mins to see if the records sync.
​
If the pending data doesn't sync please let us know!

Hello Sreejith,

Apologies about the delay in getting back to you.

Unfortunately, it isn't possible to have it deployed the way your propose - but there is another way. You know how to create a client profile? In the same option, top right, there is an option for Service Management - create this profile and activate those interaction for that profile. All Audits are Service Management profile interactions and they will be available only for this profile, nowhere else.

If you don't wish the staff to have an access to this profile, you can remove it from them in the side menu -> Administration -> Permissions -> click on the pencil next to each of the roles and remove the Service Management from the list there + save.
Thank you. I will try and get back to you if there are any concerns.

Hi Oluwatoyin, Dipeptidyl carboxypeptidase (DCP), also known as angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE), is an endogenous enzyme in the body, meaning it is naturally produced and plays a key role in regulating blood pressure through the renin-angiotensin system.

Since DCP itself is not a drug or an external substance, you cannot have a typical allergic reaction to it in the way you would to a medication or food allergen.
